15/10/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The new 300-seat parliament was sworn in on Wednesday (October 14th) after a traditional blessing ceremony, led by the Archbishop of Athens and All Greece Ieronymos II. 
Prime Minister George Papandreou, whose PASOK party won a convincing victory in the October 4th snap elections and an absolute majority of 160 seats in parliament, promised that the role of the legislature will be changed drastically "for the benefit of our nation". 
(Xinhua, ANA-MPA - 14/10/09)
